<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2008-08-26</DATELINE><TITLE>International Law and Public Health Policy</TITLE><BODY>The field of international public health and the contribution of international organizations to its development is described. The growth and elaboration of the field of international public health law in the last decade and a half is one of the most notable developments in global health policy. In this new era of global health governance, international law has an important, albeit limited, role to play in promoting and coordinating international cooperation and national action to protect and promote global health. Particular attention is paid to the global health impact of international law developed under the auspices of the World Health Organization and the World Trade Organization.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>